    b"or agent_reply message in it as direct\x0a        evidence that the reply was alrea"
    b"dy posted to the user (agent is the\x0a        persisted conversation role for an a"
    b"gent_reply action). Do not require\x0a        another \"fresh\" reply or fail merely "
    b"because the compact task output\x0a        summary does not explicitly restate that"
    b" timing. A validation_reply is\x0a        feedback from an earlier failed check, no"
    b"t proof that the current attempt\x0a        is incomplete; judge the newest task ou"
    b"tcome on its own evidence.\x0a\x0a        On a retry, the candidate result is the newe"
    b"st task attempt described by\x0a        the task output summary. Earlier agent repl"
    b"ies are superseded history.\x0a        Use validation_reply messages only as diagno"
    b"stic context about what needs\x0a        attention. Derive the expected result from"
    b" the active user request rather\x0a        than treating retry guidance as an answe"
    b"r key.\x0a\x0a        Validate both completion and result quality. For a reply task, c"
    b"onfirm\x0a        that a reply was posted, that it directly responds to the user's "
    b"request,\x0a        and that it has no demonstrable factual or logical error. Do no"
    b"t\x0a        rubber-stamp a merely non-empty reply. Equally, do not invent a strict"
    b"er\x0a        requirement, demand preferred wording, or ask for another reply after"
    b" a\x0a        satisfactory one is already present.\x0a\x0a        Use sound judgment appr"
