    b"cide which task should\x0a        run next.\x0a\x0a        When the usual appropriate tas"
    b"k would violate a user preference either follow that preferences guidance or sim"
    b"ply choose do nothing.\x0a\x0a        Stop once you have the right task.\x0a\x0a        Cont"
    b"ext sections:\x0a        - Current user request: the request being routed now.\x0a    "
    b"    - Conversation history: earlier human and agent messages.\x0a        - Session "
    b"memories: remembered observations for this session.\x0a        - User preferences: "
    b"durable user preferences that should influence routing.\x0a        - Available task"
    b"s: the only tasks that may be selected.\x0a        - Task-choice memories: remember"
    b"ed observations about choosing tasks.\x0a        - Machine state: current non-store"
    b"d local time, timezone, OS/architecture,\x0a          monitor resolutions, and IP g"
    b"eolocation.\x0a\x0a        Optional output available in this step:\x0a        - candidate"
    b"_memory: a vague remembered observation that could be useful to\x0a          preser"
    b"ve. Only include observations not commentary.\x0a\x0a        Rules:\x0a        - Select e"
    b"xactly one task from Available tasks.\x0a        - selected_task_id must exactly ma"
    b"tch an available task id.\x0a        - Do not invent task ids.\x0a        - Do not per"
    b"form the task. Only choose the task.\x0a        - Use optional outputs only when th"
    b"ey are useful.\x0a        - User request may be related to memories that this layer"
    b" is not yet aware of, simply finish your task without thinking too much if that "
    b"seems to be the case.\x0a\x0a        {{ _.role(\"user\") }}\x0a\x0a        Current user reques"
